[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-lead] West has led the \S7, which looks like a fourth-best from length, so the spades are led from a five-card suit. With nearly all the missing points likely sitting away from the opening leader, West rates to have little beyond this suit to offer the defence, so winning the \SA and cashing out is comfortable. Take your two top hearts and four diamonds, then run the club suit from the top, cashing the \AK and the long cards for four tricks; that brings you to ten. There is no finesse and no suit to set up; just cash in an order that keeps an entry to dummy's long clubs.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-play] Nine tricks were always there and the long clubs handed you a tenth simply for cashing in the right order. The skill was keeping access to dummy so the club length cashed, never a finesse. Well counted and tidily played.}
